        <p>Adding a visual state to an object is actually two sets of steps. First, you create the visual state. Then, you apply the state to the object. In order to create a visual state, you must get your object ready first. Once you create the visual state, it can be applied to that object. Visual states created for one object cannot be used on other objects.</p>
